gomodel:SYNGO_2840  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Analysis of MDGA1-NL interaction using cell-surface binding assays\"\nFig.3: \"MDGA knockdown increases inhibitory synapse density in an NL2-dependent manner in cultured neurons\"\nFig.4: \"MDGA1 overexpression decreases inhibitory, but not excitatory, synaptic transmission in cultured cortical neurons\"\nFig.5: \"MDGA1 cis expression inhibits NL2 activity in artificial synapse-formation assays and cell-adhesion assays\"\n\nCoclusion: MDGA1 is a cis-interactor with NL2 and negatively affects its transsynaptic adhesion to neurexin and its ability to induce presynapse assembly.. Experimental description: - \"Cultured hippocampal neurons were prepared from embryonic day 18 (E18) rat r mouse brain as described previously (2).\"\n- \"pGW1-MDGA1 encodes full-length human MDGA1 cloned (amino acids 1-955) \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2840" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

